title: COLLEGE VOLLEYBALL: Grenadiers roll past Carlow
text:
COLLEGE VOLLEYBALL: Grenadiers roll past Carlow News and Tribune sports department News and Tribune Posted on Oct 9, 2015 by News and Tribune Sports NEW ALBANY — IU Southeast dominated Carlow (Pa.) on Friday night at the Southeast Activities Building en route to a 25-13, 25-12, 25-15 win. IU Southeast freshman and Floyd Central graduate Hannah Joly smacked 10 kills. Teammate Michala Beasley added eight and the Grenadiers’ Katie Fischer had six. IU Southeast setter Hannah Barker had 23 assists. The Grenadiers (13-7, 7-2 Kentucky Intercollegiate Athletic Conference) had eight aces, including a career-high five from Joly. Carlow (15-10, 1-3) was able to keep the first set close for the first half of the game. It trailed 10-6 before the Grenadiers went on a 15-7 run to close out the frame. The Grenadiers opened the second set by jumping out to a comfortable lead, but Carlow was able to get back in the set at 15-11. IU Southeast responded by reeling off a 10-1 stretch to seal the set. Joly had two aces during that run. Grenadier freshman Maddie Jacobi put the match out of reach by serving seven straight points. She had an ace during that run that saw IU Southeast extend its lead from 18-13 to 23-14. Fischer had two kills during the stretch as well. The Grenadiers have won six in a row and will look for their seventh straight victory when they host Midway (Ky.) on Tuesday.
